# mark-claw: rules for AI edits (Cursor)

You are editing the **mark-claw** repo. The execution process is in
`specs/WORKFLOW.md`; the authoritative hard rules and commands are in `CLAUDE.md`; the approved
stack and per-stack rules are in your stack profile. Read those before any non-trivial change.

## Workflow guardrails

- **One driver per worktree/branch.** Do NOT make Agent/Composer edits in a worktree while a Claude
  Code session is actively working it — concurrent writers corrupt each other. Coordinate hand-offs
  (the session is suspended via a WIP-commit + `HANDOFF.md` before a human takes over).
- **Branch/PR model.** Work happens on the issue's Linear branch; one Linear issue ⇄ one branch ⇄
  one PR. Do NOT create side branches, merge to `main`, or open PRs from here unless asked.
- **Stay in scope** of the current Linear issue — its acceptance criteria are the contract. File a
  new issue rather than silently expanding scope.

## Hard rules

The authoritative hard rules live in `CLAUDE.md` and `specs/WORKFLOW.md` — never hand-edit generated
files, stay air-gapped (nothing required at runtime on a CDN/SaaS), use the approved stack only, and
respect the stack's architectural boundaries. Read those before non-trivial changes, and audit any
diff with **`/stack-check`** before opening a PR.
